The hearings into the possible impeachment of suspended public protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane continue  on Monday. Last week Mkhwebane's representative, advocate Dali Mpofu said they would call President Cyril Ramaphosa to testify at the  hearings — or, if he fails to appear, summon him before parliament. “It looks like we might even have to call other former presidents,” he said. TimesLIVE Support independent journalism by subscribing to the Sunday Times. Just R20 for the first month.